  "rationale": "<p>Choice C is correct. It&rsquo;s given that <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"P of t \"></span> represents the population of snow leopards <span class=\"italic\">t</span> years after 1990. <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"P of 30 equals 550 \"></span> corresponds to <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"t equals 30 \"></span> and <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"P of t equals 550\"></span>. It follows that <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"t equals 30 \"></span> corresponds to 30 years after 1990, or 2020. Thus, the best interpretation of <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"P of 30 equals 550 \"></span> is that the snow leopard population in this area is predicted to be 550 in the year 2020.<p>Choices A and B are incorrect and may result from reversing the interpretations of <span class=\"italic\">t</span> and <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"P of t\"></span>. Choice D is incorrect and may result from determining that 30 years after 1990 is 2030, not 2020.</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n",
